
NAME RESOLUTION 

Every host has a DNS resolution configuration file at :
$ /etc/resolv.conf

DIG and nslookup can be used for dns resolution

SWITCHING AND ROUTING IN LINUX 
To configure a gateway on one system to reach other networks, run the command:
$ ip route add 192.168.2.0/24 via  gateway at 192.168.1.1

To route to any network outside of your network, run:
$ ip route add 0.0.0.0 via ( default gateway router ip) 192.168.2.1 or ip route default via 192.168.2.1
